<style>
  /* ── Variables ── */
  .cg {
    --g: 3px;            /* gap — controls line thickness */
    --g2: calc(var(--g) * 2);
    /* For the X pattern, each triangle's apex must be pulled back from
       (50%,50%) by g/√2 so the perpendicular gap width stays constant
       all the way to the centre. Base corners shift by g*(1+1/√2). */
    --gd:  calc(var(--g) * 0.7071); /* g / √2  */
    --g17: calc(var(--g) * 1.7071); /* g * (1 + 1/√2) */
    --bar: 5.5rem;       /* width of one bar square */
    --line: var(--color-fg);
    --fill: var(--color-bg);
    font-family: serif;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  /* ── Row ── */
  .cg-row {
    display: flex;
    width: fit-content;
  }

  /* ── Bar ── */
  .cg-bar {
    width: var(--bar);
    aspect-ratio: 1;
    background: var(--line);
    position: relative;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    /* collapse the shared border between adjacent bars */
    margin-left: calc(-1 * var(--g));
  }
  .cg-bar:first-child {
    margin-left: 0;
  }

  /* ── Zones — white fills clipped to shape ── */
  .zone {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: var(--fill);
  }

  /* 1 chord: rectangle inset from all edges */
  .bar-1 .zone {
    clip-path: inset(var(--g));
  }

  /* 2 chords: single diagonal top-right → bottom-left
     Each triangle is pulled back from the diagonal by --g,
     creating a visible gap where the bar background shows through. */
  .bar-2 .zone-tl {
    clip-path: polygon(
      var(--g)  var(--g),
      calc(100% - var(--g2)) var(--g),
      var(--g)  calc(100% - var(--g2))
    );
  }
  .bar-2 .zone-br {
    clip-path: polygon(
      calc(100% - var(--g)) var(--g2),
      calc(100% - var(--g)) calc(100% - var(--g)),
      var(--g2) calc(100% - var(--g))
    );
  }

  /* 4 chords: X pattern.
     Each triangle's apex sits at 50% ± gd rather than exactly 50%,
     so the gap between adjacent zones is a constant g pixels wide
     (perpendicular to the diagonal) all the way to the centre. */
  .bar-4 .zone-top {
    clip-path: polygon(
      var(--g17) var(--g),
      calc(100% - var(--g17)) var(--g),
      50% calc(50% - var(--gd))
    );
  }
  .bar-4 .zone-right {
    clip-path: polygon(
      calc(100% - var(--g)) var(--g17),
      calc(100% - var(--g)) calc(100% - var(--g17)),
      calc(50% + var(--gd)) 50%
    );
  }
  .bar-4 .zone-bottom {
    clip-path: polygon(
      calc(100% - var(--g17)) calc(100% - var(--g)),
      var(--g17) calc(100% - var(--g)),
      50% calc(50% + var(--gd))
    );
  }
  .bar-4 .zone-left {
    clip-path: polygon(
      var(--g) calc(100% - var(--g17)),
      var(--g) var(--g17),
      calc(50% - var(--gd)) 50%
    );
  }

  /* ── Chord labels ── */
  .chord {
    position: absolute;
    line-height: 1;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .bar-1 .chord {
    inset: 0;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  /* Centroids of each triangular zone */
  .bar-2 .chord-tl { top: 33%; left: 33%; transform: translate(-50%, -50%); }
  .bar-2 .chord-br { bottom: 33%; right: 33%; transform: translate(50%, 50%); }

  .bar-4 .chord-top    { top: 20%;    left: 50%;  transform: translate(-50%, -50%); }
  .bar-4 .chord-right  { top: 50%;    right: 18%; transform: translate(50%, -50%); }
  .bar-4 .chord-bottom { bottom: 20%; left: 50%;  transform: translate(-50%, 50%); }
  .bar-4 .chord-left   { top: 50%;    left: 18%;  transform: translate(-50%, -50%); }

  /* ── Demo layout for the subdivision examples ── */
  .subdivision-demos {
    display: flex;
    gap: 2.5rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin: 1.5rem 0 2.5rem;
  }
  .subdivision-demo figcaption {
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    opacity: 0.7;
    font-family: system-ui, sans-serif;
  }

  /* ── Multi-row chart ── */
  .cg-chart {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    width: fit-content;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }
  .cg-chart .cg-row {
    margin-top: calc(-1 * var(--g));
  }
  .cg-chart .cg-row:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  /* Section label sits to the left of a row */
  .cg-section {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }
  .cg-section-label {
    font-family: system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    opacity: 0.6;
    writing-mode: vertical-rl;
    transform: rotate(180deg);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
</style>

<h1>Grille harmonique</h1>

<p>
  A <em>grille harmonique</em> is a French jazz notation style that places each bar
  inside a square, subdivided diagonally to show how many chords fall within it. This
  is an exploration of whether the style can be reproduced with HTML and CSS, as a
  potential future renderer for grigson.
</p>
<p>
  The technique: each bar is a rectangle with a dark background. Chord zones are
  overlaid as white shapes using <code>clip-path</code>, with a small gap left between
  them so the dark background shows through as lines.
</p>

<h2>Subdivision</h2>
<p>
  Each square is subdivided based on how many chords it contains. In 4/4 time, chords
  can last a whole bar, half a bar, or a quarter of a bar.
</p>

